Some questions from JS novice:<p>Why map isn&#x27;t implemented:<p><pre><code>    function map(fun, coll) {
      if (exists(coll)) return _map(fun)(coll);
      return _map(fun);
    }
</code></pre>
Why use <i>arguments</i> when you can name your parameter in declaration?<p>And why <i>_ma</i>p is defined in global scope? Shouldn&#x27;t it be better defined inside <i>map</i> function? What are up/downsides in performance for this move?
